a:18:{s:4:"name";s:7:"Colospa";s:11:"small_descr";s:256:"Colospa (Mebeverine) is used to relieve cramps or spasms of the stomach and intestines (gut). It is particularly useful in treating irritable bowel syndrome (IBS) and similar conditions. Consult your physician for further Colospa (Mebeverine) applications.";s:14:"small_descr_de";s:271:"Colospa wird verwendet, um Magen- und Darmkrampf oder Spasmus zu schwächen. Es ist besonders nützlich in der Behandlung von Reizdarmsyndrom (RDS) und ähnliche Zustände.  Bitte befragen Sie Ihren Arzt, um weitere Informationen über Colospa (Mebeverine) zu kriegen.   ";s:14:"small_descr_fr";s:343:"Colospa (Mebeverine) est utilisée pour soulager les crampes ou les spasmes de l'estomac et des intestins. Le médicament est particulièrement utilisé dans le traitement du syndrome du côlon irritable (SCI) et des conditions similaires. Consultez votre médecin pour obtenir plus d'information sur des applications de Colospa (Mebeverine) .";s:14:"small_descr_es";s:287:"Colospa (Mebeverine) es utilizada para aliviar los calambres o espasmos del estómago y los intestinos. Es particularmente útil en el tratamiento del síndrome del intestino irritable y condiciones similares. Consulte a su médico para obtener más aplicaciones de Colospa (Mebeverine).";s:14:"small_descr_it";s:281:"Colospa (Mebeverine) si usa per la soppressione dei disagio e degli spasmi dello stomaco e intestino. E' particolarmente utile nel trattamento della sindrome dell'intestino irritabile e condizioni simili. Bisogna consultare il medico per ulteriori domande sul Colospa (Mebeverine).";s:10:"full_descr";s:2309:"<p><strong>INDICATIONS</strong></p><p>Colospa prevents nerve signals passing through to the muscle in the intestines. It helps the muscle to relax, preventing painful spasm.</p><p><strong>INSTRUCTIONS</strong></p><p>Take exactly as prescribed by your Health Provider.</p><p>Take the missed dose as soon as you remember. If it is almost time for your next dose, skip the missed dose and take the medicine at the next regularly scheduled time. Do not take extra medicine to make up the missed dose.</p><p><strong>DOSAGE</strong></p><p>You should take 135 mg Colospa hydrochloride (1 tablet) 3 times a day, before meals. After a few weeks of treatment when the health-giving effect has been obtained, the dosage may be gradually lowered.</p><p><strong>STORAGE&nbsp;</strong></p><p>Store this medicine at room temperature in a tightly-closed container, away from heat and light.</p><p><strong>SAFETY INFORMATION</strong></p><p>Use Colospa with caution in the following cases: failure of function of part of the gut causing an obstruction (paralytic ileus); life long inherited blood diseases which can cause a variety of symptoms, including mental health problems (porphyrias).<br /><br /> In case you become pregnant, consult with your doctor and discuss the benefits and risks of taking Colospa while pregnancy. The safety of Colospa 135 mg in pregnancy has not been proved. In case you are or will be breast-feeding a baby while you use Colospa, consult with your doctor and discuss any possible risks to your baby. The harmful effects are not known in case this medicine is used while breastfeeding a baby.</p>
<p>Drug interactions can result in unwanted side effects or prevent a medicine from doing its job. Some medicines or medical conditions may interact with this medicine. Inform your doctor or pharmacist of all prescription and over-the-counter medicine that you are taking.</p><p><strong>SIDE EFFECTS</strong></p><p>You should consult with your doctor in case you have any of side effects especially bothersome listed below: Constipation, confusion, agitation.</p>
<p>For more information about any other possible risks associated with this medicine, please read the information provided with the medicine or consult your doctor or pharmacist.</p>
<p>The symptoms of overdosage are not known.</p>";s:13:"full_descr_de";s:0:"";s:13:"full_descr_fr";s:0:"";s:13:"full_descr_es";s:0:"";s:13:"full_descr_it";s:0:"";s:9:"min_price";s:8:"0.872025";s:9:"pack_name";s:5:"pills";s:4:"type";s:2:"mg";s:7:"analogs";N;s:8:"synonims";a:41:{i:0;s:5:"Veron";i:1;s:6:"Verine";i:2;s:7:"Verimed";i:3;s:11:"Spasmotalin";i:4;s:10:"Spasmopriv";i:5;s:9:"Spasmonal";i:6;s:9:"Spasmerin";i:7;s:7:"Rudakol";i:8;s:6:"Rostil";i:9;s:8:"Meverine";i:10;s:4:"Meva";i:11;s:7:"Menosor";i:12;s:10:"Medoverine";i:13;s:9:"Meditoina";i:14;s:17:"Mebeverixx lyssia";i:15;s:11:"Mebeverinum";i:16;s:10:"Mebeverina";i:17;s:9:"Mebeverin";i:18;s:7:"Mebetin";i:19;s:8:"Meberine";i:20;s:4:"Mave";i:21;s:5:"Manil";i:22;s:6:"Iriban";i:23;s:7:"Irbosyd";i:24;s:10:"Gastromins";i:25;s:6:"Evarin";i:26;s:6:"Evadol";i:27;s:10:"Duspaverin";i:28;s:8:"Duspatin";i:29;s:10:"Duspatalin";i:30;s:8:"Duspatal";i:31;s:8:"Duspamen";i:32;s:10:"Doloverina";i:33;s:7:"Colotal";i:34;s:11:"Colospasmin";i:35;s:8:"Colospas";i:36;s:8:"Colopriv";i:37;s:7:"Colofac";i:38;s:6:"Colese";i:39;s:8:"Bevispas";i:40;s:5:"Arluy";}s:18:"active_ingredients";N;s:8:"packings";a:1:{i:135;a:7:{i:5114;a:5:{s:10:"id_packing";s:4:"5114";s:5:"count";s:2:"30";s:6:"dosage";d:135;s:14:"price_per_pill";s:6:"1.1325";s:4:"name";s:7:"Colospa";}i:5115;a:5:{s:10:"id_packing";s:4:"5115";s:5:"count";s:2:"60";s:6:"dosage";d:135;s:14:"price_per_pill";s:7:"0.99042";s:4:"name";s:7:"Colospa";}i:5116;a:5:{s:10:"id_packing";s:4:"5116";s:5:"count";s:2:"90";s:6:"dosage";d:135;s:14:"price_per_pill";s:7:"0.94306";s:4:"name";s:7:"Colospa";}i:5117;a:5:{s:10:"id_packing";s:4:"5117";s:5:"count";s:3:"120";s:6:"dosage";d:135;s:14:"price_per_pill";s:7:"0.91938";s:4:"name";s:7:"Colospa";}i:5118;a:5:{s:10:"id_packing";s:4:"5118";s:5:"count";s:3:"180";s:6:"dosage";d:135;s:14:"price_per_pill";s:6:"0.8957";s:4:"name";s:7:"Colospa";}i:5119;a:5:{s:10:"id_packing";s:4:"5119";s:5:"count";s:3:"270";s:6:"dosage";d:135;s:14:"price_per_pill";s:7:"0.87992";s:4:"nam